## Node / npm hygiene (CRITICAL)
# `node_modules/` must never be committed:
# - It is OS/CPU/Node-version dependent (breaks reproducible builds across machines/CI/Docker).
# - It is huge/noisy, slows clones and code review, and often contains native binaries.
# - Lockfiles exist specifically to reproduce installs deterministically from `package.json`.
